\item \emph{\code{6}} components: \code{bvb}, \code{hfx}, \code{jqt}, \code{ntq}, \code{rhn}, and \code{xhk}.
}

Multiplying the sizes of these groups together produces \emph{\code{54}}.

Find the three wires you need to disconnect in order to divide the
components into two separate groups. \emph{What do you get if you multiply
the sizes of these two groups together?}

